    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "6b65712b_e820127e",
        "filename": "autoroll/config/chromite-chromium.json",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 6,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-12T19:12:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So these are both display names, the top-level one controls what\u0027s displayed on the server UI and in notifications, and this one controls what shows up in commit messages.  If I were writing this from scratch, they would be the same thing, but I didn\u0027t want to change the commit message too much, especially the subject line.  Currently we use the childPath from the RepoManager for this (which is nonsensical for some rollers, hence the change).  Not sure how many people (if any) would complain if we just switched to using the top-level childName, eg. \"Roll Chromite from A to B\".  I guess I could poll the (now very large) list of clients.\n\nI don\u0027t feel strongly about the name of the field, but calling it \"childDisplayName\" to differentiate from \"childName\", which is also a display name, seems confusing too.  Changing the top-level one to \"childDisplayName\" and this one to \"childDisplayNameForCommitMessage\" would be clear but way too verbose.  I think I felt okay about calling them the same thing because I thought that \"childName\" under \"commitMsg\" implied that this was the display name for commit messages only, whereas \"childName\" at the top level is for everything else.  I dunno.  I\u0027m open to suggestions.",
      "parentUuid": "369dde9c_d166a17c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 6,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 6,
        "endChar": 14
      },
      "revId": "66a17d69912fbdff727c9d9ec1fb52b6ee7b433e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b1fb9544_7158ff07",
        "filename": "autoroll/config/chromite-chromium.json",
        "patchSetId": 12
      },
      "lineNbr": 6,
      "author": {
        "id": 5145
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-13T15:21:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yea I was confused with commit msg child name and UI display child name, for some reason I assumed their were both the same but they are not the same.\n\n\u003e  I thought that \"childName\" under \"commitMsg\" implied that this was the display name for commit messages only, whereas \"childName\" at the top level is for everything else. \n\nI agree having childName under commitMsg implies that it is for commit messages only. I guess it would remove confusion if the top-level one was called something else, right now it is not clear what that is used for (childDisplayName actually SGTM). But I guess we always had that problem so maybe not that important.",
      "parentUuid": "6b65712b_e820127e",
