      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-05-12T19:12:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sure, removed it.  I\u0027m not sure what we\u0027ll do in the future if we need something like this.  For a similar scenario, we could add sanitizers to the config, basically regex find and replace.  But that may not necessarily cover all cases, for example we might have a github roller which creates a commit for each revision in the roll, and we may therefore need to run the sanitizer over the individual revisions as well.  Hard to say.  For now I\u0027m inclined to just hope it doesn\u0027t come up, and determine the best approach if it does.",
      "parentUuid": "73075daf_aca33b69",
